  "members": "Mikhail Larionov and Natalia Goncharova",
  "text": "Rayonism is a style of abstract art that developed in Russia in 1911. The Rayonists sought an art that floated beyond abstraction, outside time and space, and to break the barriers between the artist and the public. They derived the name from the use of dynamic rays of contrasting color, representing lines of reflected light — crossing of reflected rays from various objects."
}, {
