  "text": "Ukrainian avant-garde - term widely used to refer the most innovative metamorphosises in Ukrainian art from the end of 1900s to the middle of the 1930s along with associated artists. Broadly it is Ukrainian art synchronized with the international avant-garde first of all in sculpture, painting, literature, cinema, theater, stage design, graphics, music, architecture."
